<p>Board advisory is a significant investment, but governance failures are far more costly. Poor board dynamics, strategic missteps, stakeholder conflict, and governance crises often cost organizations multiples of what effective advisory would have cost. The value calculation should focus on risk mitigation and improved decision quality, not just the advisory fee.</p>

<p><strong>Typical engagement structures include:</strong> project-based work for specific challenges (board effectiveness reviews, governance design, crisis response); retained advisory for ongoing support (monthly or quarterly sessions); and intensive support during critical periods (leadership transitions, major strategic decisions, organizational change).</p>

<p>Investment is discussed transparently during the discovery phase, ensuring alignment before any commitment.</p>`
